<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,603,1025]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,783,809]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
The RBINS kindly provided 
<specimenCount box="[644,804,783,809]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">four paratypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Orchymont" authorityName="Orchymont" box="[841,1196,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillus">
<emphasis box="[841,1059,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Hydrochus pupillus</emphasis>
Orchymont
</taxonomicName>
, which are part of the Orchymont collection. Unfortunately, the 
<typeStatus box="[618,716,819,845]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
could not be found. The 
<typeStatus box="[993,1100,819,845]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">paratypes</typeStatus>
consist of 
<specimenCount box="[1221,1337,819,845]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
, and 
<specimenCount pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
. The 
<specimenCount box="[306,422,855,881]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
have been dissected, and are conspecific. The females appear to also represent the same species. I have selected one of the males to image the habitus and male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1067,1151,890,917]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–51" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[175,1422,203,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-15@77.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 50–51. Habitus and male genitalia. 50. Hydrochus pupillus Orchymont, paratype. 51. Hydrochus drechseli Makhan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5043340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5043340/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[1171,1315,891,918]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="301 - 341" refId="ref50713" refString="Oliva, A. (1996) The genus Hydrochus Leach (Coleoptera: Hydrophiloidea: Hydrochidae) in South America, with special reference to Argentina. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 132, 301 - 341." type="journal article" year="1996">Oliva (1996)</bibRefCitation>
also noted the 
<specimenCount box="[192,356,927,953]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">four paratypes</specimenCount>
, but did not mention anything about the 
<typeStatus box="[810,912,927,953]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1437,603,1025]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[448,657,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soekhnandanae">
<emphasis box="[448,657,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. soekhnandanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[714,839,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillus">
<emphasis box="[714,839,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. pupillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinctively differ. Refer to the images of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soekhnandanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. soekhnandanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Perkins, P. D." box="[297,476,999,1025]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref50913" refString="Perkins, P. D. (2019 c) Taxonomy of Venezuelan water beetles in the genus Hydrochus Leach, 1817, and an analysis of male genitalia morphology (Coleoptera: Hydrochidae). Zootaxa, 4708 (1), 1 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4708.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Perkins (2019c)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[530,654,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupillus">
<emphasis box="[530,654,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">H. pupillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein (
<figureCitation box="[747,831,998,1025]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–51" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[175,1422,203,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-15@77.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 50–51. Habitus and male genitalia. 50. Hydrochus pupillus Orchymont, paratype. 51. Hydrochus drechseli Makhan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5043340" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5043340/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
